S'  We propose that memory effects in the conductivity of metallic systems can be\nproduced by the same two levels systems that are responsible for the 1/f noise.\nMemory effects are extremely long-lived responses of the conductivity to\nchanges in external parameters such as density or magnetic field. Using the\nquantum transport theory, we derive a universal relationship between the memory\neffect and the 1/f noise. Finally, we propose a magnetic memory effect, where\nthe magneto-resistance is sensitive to the history of the applied magnetic\nfield.\n'
