S'  This paper deals with the so-called staircasing phenomenon, which frequently\narises in total variation based denoising models in image analysis. We prove in\nparticular that staircasing always occurs at global extrema of the datum and at\nall extrema of the minimizer. It is also shown that, for radial images, the\nstaircasing always appears at the extrema and at the boundary of the image. We\nalso prove the equivalence between the denoising model and the total variation\nflow, in the radial case, thus extending a previous result in dimension one.\nThis equivalence cannot hold in the nonradial case, as it is shown with a\ncounterexample. This connection allows us to understand how the staircase zones\nand the discontinuities of the denoising problem evolve with the regularization\nparameter.\n'
