S'  We state a generalization of the Connes-Tretkoff-Moscovici Rearrangement\nLemma and give a surprisingly simple (almost trivial) proof of it. Secondly, we\nput on a firm ground the multivariable functional calculus used implicitly in\nthe Rearrangement Lemma and elsewhere in the recent modular curvature paper by\nConnes and Moscovici. Furthermore, we show that the fantastic formulas\nconnecting the one and two variable modular functions of loc. cit. are just\nexamples of the plenty recursion formulas which can be derived from the\ncalculus of divided differences. We show that the functions derived from the\nmain integral occurring in the Rearrangement Lemma can be expressed in terms of\ndivided differences of the Logarithm, generalizing the "modified Logarithm" of\nConnes-Tretkoff.\n  Finally, we show that several expansion formulas derived from the Magnus\nexpansion have a conceptual explanation in terms of a multivariable functional\ncalculus applied to divided differences.\n'
