S'  Dynamics of DNA bubbles is of interest for both statistical physics and\nbiology. We present exact solutions to the Fokker-Planck equation governing the\ndynamics in presence of a long-range entropic interaction. Meeting time and\nmeeting position probability distributions for all times and positions are\nderived from the solutions. Probability distribution functions reflect the\nvalue of the loop exponent of the entropic interaction. Our results extend\nprevious results concentrating mainly on the tails of the probability\ndistribution functions and open a way to determining the strength of the\nentropic interaction experimentally which has been a matter of discussion\nrecently. Using numerical simulations, we also discuss the influence of the\nfinite size of a DNA chain on the bubble dynamics. Analogous results are\nobtained as well in the case of subdiffusive dynamics of a DNA bubble in a\nheteropolymer, revealing highly universal asymptotics of meeting time and\nposition probability functions.\n'
